<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900507-0048</DOCNO><DOCID>900507-0048.</DOCID><HL>   Who's News:   Manville Reorganizes   Some of Its Businesses</HL><DATE>05/07/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6</SO><CO>   WNEWS MVL</CO><LP>   DENVER -- Manville Corp. reorganized some of itsoperations and named two new group presidents as part of acontinuing effort to define its core businesses and betterfocus its marketing efforts.   The maker of wood, paper and fiberglass products namedRichard A. Kashnow president of the new Engineered ProductsGroup, which will make and market the company's fiberglassmats, reinforcement fibers, and auto and aerospace filtersand insulation parts. Manville's Glaswerk Schuller unit inWest Germany will also be part of the group. Mr. Kashnow wasvice president and general manager of the former mats, fiberand reinforcements division at Manville.</LP><TEXT>   Ronald W. Mathewson was named president of the newBuilding Products Group, which will combine the company'sfiberglass-roofing and building-insulation businesses. He wasvice president and general manager of the company's formerbuilding insulation division.   Messrs. Kashnow and Mathewson were also named senior vicepresidents of the corporation.   John D.C. Roach, an executive vice president, was namedpresident of the new Mining and Minerals Group, includingfiltration and minerals production worldwide.   Robert Anderson was named senior vice president forscience and technology. He will be in charge of health,safety, environment and research departments at the company.He succeeds William A. Sells, who has announced his plans toretire.   Manville Forest Products Corp. will continue to operate asa unit, headed by President Thomas Johnson, who assumed thattitle late last year.</TEXT></DOC>